UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1436
1 AN ACT relating to barbering.
2 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
3 Section 1. KRS 317.430 is amended to read as follows:
4 (1) There is hereby created an independent agency of the state government to be known
5 as the Kentucky Board of Barbering, which shall have complete supervision over
6 the administration of the provisions of this chapter relating to barbers, barbering,
7 barber shops, mobile barber shops, independent contract owners, barber schools,
8 and the teaching of barbering.
9 (2) (a) The board shall be composed of five (5) voting members appointed by the
10 Governor. Four (4) of these members shall be barbers holding a valid license
11 and practicing in Kentucky. One (1) of these members[member] shall be a
12 citizen at large who is not associated with or financially interested in
13 barbering. At all times in the filling of vacancies of voting membership on the
14 barber board, this balance of representation shall be maintained.
15 (b) The executive director employed under Section 3 of this Act shall be a
16 nonvoting member of the board. He or she may be counted in determining a
17 quorum, but shall not vote on matters before the board.
18 (3) [The two (2) members appointed to fill the terms beginning on February 1, 2008,
19 shall serve until February 1, 2011, and the three (3) members appointed to fill the
20 terms beginning on February 1, 2007, shall serve until February 1, 2010. ]All
21 [subsequent ]appointments shall be for a term of three (3) years, with terms ending
22 on February 1.
23 (4) The Governor shall not remove any voting member of the board except for cause.
24 (5) The board shall elect from its voting members one (1) to serve as chair[chairman],
25 one (1) to serve as vice chair[chairman], and one[a third] to serve as secretary.
26 (6) Three (3) members shall constitute a quorum for the transaction of business.
27 (7) In addition to the other qualifications specified in this section, voting barber
Page 1 of 8
