UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1436
1 members of the board shall be at least twenty-three (23) years of age, citizens of the
2 United States, residents of Kentucky, and shall[must] have engaged in the practice
3 of barbering in this state for a period of at least five (5) years.
4 (8) A[No] member of the board shall not be financially interested in, or have any
5 financial connection with, any barber or cosmetology school, wholesale cosmetic or
6 barber supply or equipment business, and[nor] shall not[any member of the barber
7 board] teach barbering, cosmetology, or manicuring for monetary considerations.
8 (9) Each voting member of the board shall receive a compensation of one hundred
9 dollars ($100) per day for each day of attendance at a meeting of the board, and
10 shall be reimbursed for necessary traveling expenses.
11 (10) The board shall hold its meetings within the state and when deemed necessary by
12 the board to discharge its duties.
13 Section 2. KRS 317.450 is amended to read as follows:
14 (1) (a) The board shall issue an apprentice license to practice barbering to any person
15 who:
16 1. Is at least seventeen and one-half (17-1/2) years of age;
17 2. [Is of good moral character and temperate habit;
18 3. ]Possesses a high school diploma, a High School Equivalency Diploma,
19 or a transcript from an issuing institution that is recognized by the
20 educational authority in the state from which the diploma, certificate, or
21 transcript is issued;
22 3.[4.] Has graduated from a licensed school of barbering;
23 4.[5.] Has satisfactorily passed the apprentice examination prescribed by the
24 barber board, which shall include a practical assessment of the
25 applicant's skills, including but not limited to a taper haircut, shampoo,
26 straight razor facial shave, facial, and a chemical application; and
27 5.[6.] Has paid a fee as established in administrative regulations promulgated
Page 2 of 8
XXXX 12/23/2025 4:10 PM Jacketed

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1436
1 by the board in accordance with KRS Chapter 13A.
2 (b) A barber shall serve an apprentice period of at least six (6) months but not
3 more than nine (9) months of continuous service from the effective date of the
4 license issued pursuant to paragraph (a) of this subsection.
5 (c) In addition to the grounds for disciplinary action specified in KRS 317.590,
6 the board may, during the apprentice period, require a licensee to retake any
7 part or all of the written or practical examination, or both.
8 (d) At the end of the apprentice period, the board shall issue a license to practice
9 barbering to an apprentice licensee who has:
10 1. Satisfactorily passed the barber examination prescribed by the board by
11 administrative regulations promulgated in accordance with KRS Chapter
12 13A; and
13 2. Complied with all other requirements of this subsection.
14 (e) The board may issue a barber license by endorsement to a resident of another
15 state, district, or territory within the United States of America upon payment
16 of a fee as established in administrative regulations promulgated by the board
17 in accordance with KRS Chapter 13A, and upon submission of satisfactory
18 evidence that the requirements for licensure in the other state are substantially
19 equivalent to the requirements of this state at the time of application. In the
20 absence of the required equivalency, an applicant from another state, district,
21 or territory within the United States of America, shall show proof of one (1)
22 year[three (3) years] or more experience immediately before making
23 application and be currently licensed and in good standing with the state,
24 district, or territory in which he or she is licensed. The board may also require
25 an applicant under this paragraph[section] to pass a written and practical
26 examination to establish equivalency.
27 (2) The board shall:
Page 3 of 8
