UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1436
1 (a) Issue a license to operate a barber shop or mobile barber shop to any barber
2 licensed under the provisions of this chapter upon application and payment of
3 a fee as established in administrative regulations promulgated by the board in
4 accordance with KRS Chapter 13A;
5 (b) Refuse to issue the license upon a failure of the licensed barber to comply
6 with the provisions of this chapter or the administrative regulations
7 promulgated by the board;
8 (c) Allow the licensed owner of a barber shop or mobile barber shop, which is
9 licensed under this chapter, to rent or lease space in his or her barber shop to
10 an independent contract owner; and
11 (d) Allow an unlicensed owner of a barber shop to rent or lease space in his or her
12 barber shop to an independent contract owner, only if the shop owner has a
13 licensed barber as a manager of the shop at all times. If the owner, manager,
14 or location of a barber shop changes, the required form and fee shall be
15 submitted to the board.
16 (3) The board shall issue a license to operate a school of barbering to any person, firm,
17 or corporation who or which:
18 (a) Applies for a license upon forms furnished by the board;
19 (b) Has the equipment and facilities that may be required by administrative
20 regulations promulgated by the board;
21 (c) Has furnished adequate evidence to the board that:
22 1. There is an intent to establish a bona fide school for the education and
23 training of competent barbers; and
24 2. A sufficient number of teachers licensed by the board will be employed
25 to conduct the school, including at least one (1) teacher with a minimum
26 of twelve (12) months' experience teaching in a barber school that
27 includes administrative experience; and
Page 4 of 8
