UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1436
1 (d) Pays a fee as established in administrative regulations promulgated by the
2 board in accordance with KRS Chapter 13A.
3 (4) The board shall issue a student permit to any person enrolled in a licensed barber
4 school upon payment of a fee as established in administrative regulations
5 promulgated by the board in accordance with KRS Chapter 13A.
6 (5) The board shall issue a license to teach barbering to any person who:
7 (a) [Is of good moral character and temperate habit;
8 (b) ]Possesses a high school diploma or a High School Equivalency Diploma;
9 (b)[(c)] Has been a Kentucky-licensed and practicing barber for at least eighteen
10 (18) months;
11 (c)[(d)] Has satisfactorily passed the examination prescribed by the board by
12 promulgation of administrative regulations; and
13 (d)[(e)] Has paid a fee as established in administrative regulations promulgated
14 by the board in accordance with KRS Chapter 13A.
15 (6) The board shall issue a license to any barber who holds an independent contract
16 owner's license who:
17 (a) [Is of good moral character and temperate habit;
18 (b) ]Possesses a high school diploma or a High School Equivalency Diploma;
19 (b)[(c)] Is a licensed and practicing barber under this chapter; and
20 (c)[(d)] Has paid a fee as established in administrative regulations promulgated
21 by the board in accordance with KRS Chapter 13A.
22 (7) The board shall issue a demonstration charity event permit to any licensed barber
23 who pays a fee as established in administrative regulations promulgated by the
24 board in accordance with KRS Chapter 13A.
25 (8) Applications for examination required in this section shall be accompanied by an
26 examination fee as established in administrative regulations promulgated by the
27 board in accordance with KRS Chapter 13A.
