1 (9) (a) On and after July 1, 2016, a license issued pursuant to this section shall expire
2 on the first day of July next following the date of its issuance. A license shall
3 be renewed on June 1 through July 1 of each year.
4 (b) Any license shall automatically be renewed by the board:
5 1. Upon receipt of the application for renewal or duplicate renewal
6 application form and the required annual renewal license fee submitted
7 either in person or via written or electronic means; and
8 2. If the applicant for renewal is otherwise in compliance with the
9 provisions of this chapter and the administrative regulations of the
10 board.
11 (10) The annual renewal license fee for each type of license renewal shall be as
12 established in administrative regulations promulgated by the board in accordance
13 with KRS Chapter 13A.
14 (11) (a) The fee per year for the renewal of an expired license, if the period of
15 expiration does not exceed five (5) years, shall be as established by
16 administrative regulations promulgated by the board in accordance with KRS
17 Chapter 13A.
18 (b) An applicant who fails to renew a license within five (5) years of its
19 expiration shall comply with the requirements for relicensure established by
20 the board through promulgation of administrative regulations in accordance
21 with KRS Chapter 13A.
22 Section 3. KRS 317.470 is amended to read as follows:
23 (1) The board:
24 (a) May employ such personnel as may be reasonably necessary to carry out the
25 provisions of this chapter, whose compensation shall be established by the
26 Personnel Cabinet; and[. The board]
27 (b) Shall by appropriate order employ an executive director[administrator] who
