1 shall be charged with responsibility of administering the provisions of this
2 chapter, and the policies of the board relating to barbering. The executive
3 director[administrator] may receive compensation as may be established by
4 classification of the position by the Personnel Cabinet.
5 (2) The board shall prescribe the duties of the[such] personnel employed by it.
6 (3) The board shall publish or electronically provide copies of its administrative[rules
7 and] regulations and any proposed amendments to all persons licensed by it and to
8 any other persons, places, or agencies as may be required by law or deemed by it
9 reasonably necessary in the administration of the provisions of this chapter.
10 Section 4. KRS 317.540 is amended to read as follows:
11 A[No] license shall not be renewed or issued by the board to any barber school[,] unless
12 the school provides:
13 (1) The name of the proposed school;
14 (2) A statement that the proposed school is authorized to operate educational programs
15 beyond secondary education;
16 (3) As a prerequisite of graduation, a prescribed course of instruction of not less than
17 one thousand two hundred (1,200)[fifteen hundred (1,500)] hours shall be given
18 within a reasonable period with not more than ten (10)[eight (8)] hours nor less than
19 four (4) hours of instruction a day, exclusive of Sundays;
20 (4) Courses of instruction in histology of the hair, skin, muscles, and nerves of the face
21 and neck; elementary chemistry with emphasis on sterilization and antiseptics;
22 disease of the skin, hair, and glands; massaging and manipulating of the muscles of
23 the upper body; cutting, shaving, arranging, dressing, coloring, bleaching, and
24 tinting the hair and such other courses as may be prescribed by administrative
25 regulation of the board; and
26 (5) Such facilities, equipment, materials, and qualified teachers as may be required by
27 administrative[rules and] regulations of the board adopted pursuant to this chapter,
